HEADWORD: Quinquenerved
<hw>Quin"que*nerved`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Quinque-</ets> + <ets>nerve</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having five nerves; -- said of a leaf with five nearly equal nerves
or ribs rising from the end of the petiole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quinquennalia</ent>⟦br⟧
